<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-11-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                        <head>No. 813.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Russell</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-11-25"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 25,
                                    1874</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 31, of the 6th instant,
                            has been received. It relates to the benevolent conduct of Messrs. H. L.
                            Boulton &amp; Co., toward immigrants from this country in distress in
                            Venezuela. The course of those gentlemen in this instance does them
                            honor, and you will offer them the thanks of this Government
                            therefor.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                        <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>